            </li>
            <li class="mb-2">
                <p><b>Procedure records</b> detail the specific medical procedures and treatments that patients undergo. These records include information about the type of procedure, the date it was performed, the healthcare providers involved, and any complications or outcomes. Procedure records are important for documenting the care provided to patients, supporting clinical decision-making, and ensuring that patients receive appropriate follow-up care.</p>
